==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gnu
<hw>Gnu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hottentot <ets>gnu</ets>,
or <ets>nju</ets>: cf. F. <ets>gnou</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of two species of large South African antelopes of the genus
<gen>Catoblephas</gen>, having a mane and bushy tail, and curved horns
in both sexes.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>gnoo</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>common gnu</xex> or <xex>wildebeest</xex>
(<spn>Catoblephas gnu</spn>) is plain brown; the <xex>brindled gnu</xex>
or <xex>blue wildebeest</xex> (<spn>C. gorgon</spn>) is larger, with
transverse stripes of black on the neck and shoulders.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Go</ent>⟦br⟧
